  id: Accessory_Carpal_Bone_L
  partName: Accessory Carpal Bone Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The Accessory Carpal Bone Left is a prominent projection on the caudal side of
    the carpal joint, serving as an attachment point for ligaments and tendons. It
    plays a critical role in stabilizing the wrist during weight-bearing and locomotion.
  - This bone helps resist excessive flexion and supports controlled movement of
    the forelimb. Its structural positioning allows efficient force transmission
    during running and jumping, contributing to overall limb strength, joint stability,
    and coordinated forelimb function.
